'''''Star Wars: The Official Magazine'' 8''' was the 8th issue of the ''[[Star Wars: The Official Magazine]]'', covering [[June]] and [[July]] [[1997]] and containing 66 pages.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*[[Feel the Force]] {{C|[[Prequel Update]]}}
*[[Jawa's Corner|Jawas' Corner]]
*Role-playing Round Up
*[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]
*Q&A

===Features===
*"[[The Legend Continues]]" {{C|by [[Jim Swallow]]}}
*:<small>We quiz [[Industrial Light & Magic|ILM's]] top people over [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']] [[The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition|Special Editions]].</small>
*"[[The Making of Star Wars (feature)|The Making of ''Star Wars'']]: Rebel Forces" {{C|by [[Dan Abnett]]}}
*:<small>The story behind the effect techniques developed for the film, and the problems faced by the ILM pioneers&hellip;</small>
*"[[Made Over]]" {{C|by [[Joe Nazarro]]}}
*:<small>An interview with [[Stuart Freeborn]], the acclaimed make-up artist responsible for some of the most familiar [[Alien/Legends|extra-terrestrial]] characters in the [[original trilogy]].</small>
*[[Dark Forces Players Guide|''Dark Forces'' Players Guide]] {{C|by [[Matt Yeo]]}}
*:<small>The [[Wikipedia:PlayStation|PlayStation]] version of Dark Forces is one of the biggest Star Wars video games ever released in this country &ndash; our players' guide (and cheat codes) should see you through any tricky bits!</small>
*"Return of the Jedi" {{C|by [[Marcus Hearn]]}}
*:<small>A report from the royal première of the Star Wars Special Edition - the pics, the quotes, and exclusive interviews with the celebs!</small>
*"[[A Long Time Ago... (David Hanks)|A Long Time Ago...]]" {{C|by [[David Hanks]]}}
*:<small>Rewind 20 years to the British premiere [sic] of the original [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|Star Wars]] &ndash; what were the events leading up to the launch of the most successful film ever made?</small>
*[[Anthony Daniels' Set Diary]]: Armless Fun
*:<small>[[Anthony Daniels]]' memories of playing [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] in the original Star Wars continue.</small>
*"[[Star Wars Kits|''Star Wars'' Kits]]" {{C|by [[Mat Irvine]]}}
*:<small>The first of our exhaustive merchandise guides &ndash; this issue, a complete listing of Star Wars model kits.</small>
*"[[Shadow Stalker]]" Part 2
*:<small>Following [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] briefing, [[Wrenga Jixton|Jix]] turns [[Assassin/Legends|assassin]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Corulag/Legends|Corulag]]&hellip;</small>
*"[[Rogue Artist]]" {{C|by [[Iain Lowson]]}}
*:<small>From a job in [[Wikipedia:Forbidden Planet (bookstore)|Forbidden Planet]] to a top gig illustrating American Star Wars comics &ndash; the meteoric rise of [[Wikipedia:Glasgow|Glasgow's]] [[Gary Erskine]].</small>

